Hot Water Plant & Return Pumps
Hot water plant
Installation – refer to installation checklist for hot and cold water.
Testing – Pressure tested to1500kpa or 1.5 times working pressure whichever is greater.
Flue installed as per manufacturer's specification.
Power flue turned on.
Temp relief points ran to tundishes.
Temperature probe from control box installed into storage tanks.
Check that an adequate water supply is available to the hot water system.
Water supply pressure shall not exceed the maximum pressure stated by manufacturer.
Open cold water inlet valve, hot water outlet valve
Exercise all valves and ensure correct operation. Ensure all valves are in open position prior turning power on.
Check the system is fully charged & all air is bled from the system & no leaks are evident
Ensure hot water heaters and storage tanks are full of water and all valves are open.
Ensure pressures are not greater than 750 Kpa to the heaters or storage tanks.
Open all individual gas isolation valves & purge gas lines.
Test gas pipe work for leaks.
Check the gas supply pressure at the inlet to the water heater with the water heater and all
range is NG: 1.13Kpa - 3.5Kpa & LPG: 2.75Kpa - 3.5Kpa
Clean filters and strainers once after 4 hours of use.
Set temperature to 65 degrees.
Hot Water Return Pumps
Hot Water Return Pumps - Installation – refer to installation checklist for hot and cold water.
Testing – Pressure tested to1500kpa or 1.5 times working pressure whichever is greater.
Ensure there is water supply to the pumps.
Clean filters and strainers once after 4 hours of use.
Turn on power to the pumps. Set the pumps to alternate.
Purge pumps of air. Ensure water is visible from the purging points.
Set balancing valves.
Inspect system for any leaks or faults.
